#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:340
msgid "Expiry Actions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:341
msgid "When a post expires, one of the following actions will occur based on your settings:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:343
msgid "The post is moved to trash and no longer visible to visitors."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:344
msgid "The post is permanently deleted from your site."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:345
msgid "The post is changed to draft status and hidden from visitors."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:346
msgid "The post is changed to private status and only visible to logged-in users with appropriate permissions."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:347
msgid "The post is moved to a specific archive category. Configure the category in the Settings tab."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:350
msgid "Post Type Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:351
msgid "Use the Settings tab to choose which post types support expiry dates. You can either enable expiry on specific post types or disable it on specific types while enabling it on all others."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:353
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:355
msgid "The Post Expiry metabox is not showing on my posts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:357
msgid "Check that \"Enable post expiry\" is ticked on the Settings tab."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:358
msgid "Check that the post type (e.g. Post, Page) is selected in the Post types list."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:359
msgid "The metabox appears in the sidebar on the right when editing a post."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:362
msgid "When does the expiry action occur?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:363
msgid "Post expiry is processed by WordPress scheduled events (cron). The action will occur shortly after the expiry date and time passes. The exact timing depends on your site traffic and WordPress cron configuration."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:365
msgid "Can I disable expiry for a specific post?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:366
msgid "Yes. Simply leave the expiry date and time fields empty in the Post Expiry metabox."
msgstr ""

